  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). NOTE: The operating envelope was expanded in Q4 2025 to include paediatric flow regimes (0.8–2.5 L/min) and higher rotational speeds (up to 4 200 RPM) following post-market surveillance findings; re-validation against the expanded envelope is planned but has not yet been completed.",
